AB  - The rapid development of artificial intelligence (AI) and generative artificial intelligence (GAI) tools, as well as their adoption in higher education (HE), has sparked particular interest in the scientific community. In 2024, publications on this subject in the Scopus database increased by 58 %. The aim of this paper is to review this literature through a methodology that integrates the PRISMA model for information retrieval and bibliometric tools as indicators of quantity and quality, as well as network maps to establish thematic trends. A total of 656 documents indexed in Scopus were analyzed. The results indicate the behavior of publication by year, the most representative countries, journals and authors. Collaboration between countries is also analyzed and ten topics that have been strongly explored are established. Finally, some gaps are presented that may lead to future studies in the field, allowing for a deeper understanding of this phenomenon.
